  "prompt": "How do you use Google Account Recovery to reset your password?",
  "response": "Here's how to use Google Account Recovery to reset your password:\n\n1. **Navigate to Account Recovery**: Go to the Google Account Recovery page by visiting `https://accounts.google.com/signin/recovery`.\n\n2. **Enter Your Email or Phone Number**: Input the email address or phone number associated with your Google account and click \"Next.\"\n\n3. **Confirm You Forgot Your Password**: When prompted, confirm that you forgot your password by clicking on the appropriate option.\n\n4. **Verification Steps**:\n   - **Get a Verification Code**: Google may ask to send a verification code to your recovery email address or phone number. Choose the one that's accessible to you.\n   - **Account Recovery Questions**: If you don\u2019t have access to your recovery options, you might be prompted to answer security questions or provide information that you previously set up.\n\n5. **Enter the Verification Code**: If you received a code by email or text, enter it in the field provided on the recovery page.\n\n6. **Set a New Password**: Once your account is verified, you will be prompted to create a new password. Enter a strong, unique password and then confirm it.\n\n7. **Complete the Process**: Follow any additional on-screen instructions to complete the process and regain access to your account.\n\n8. **Update Account Information**: After you reset your password, consider updating your account recovery information (e.g., phone number, recovery email) in case you need to use them for future recoveries.\n\nIf you encounter any issues or need further assistance during the recovery process, Google provides additional support and detailed instructions which can be accessed through the help and support sections on their website.",
